<% content_for :title, "Okkle Privacy Policy — Okkle Find" %>

<section class="page-head legal-page-head">
  <p class="hero-eyebrow">Privacy policy</p>
  <h1 class="page-title">Okkle Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Last updated: June 29, 2026</p>
</section>

<div class="legal-page">
  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Okkle helps self-employed UK couriers track mileage, earnings, expenses, receipts and estimated tax information. Okkle is a record-keeping tool and does not provide tax advice or file tax returns.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>Data Stored In The App</h2>
    <p>Okkle may store profile settings, vehicle settings, trip records, mileage, route details, earnings, expenses, receipt images, pay screenshots, backup status and tax estimate inputs on your device.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>How Data Is Used</h2>
    <p>Your data is used to show records, calculate estimates, generate exports, create backup files, support reminders and power app features you choose to use.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>Location, Motion, Camera And Photos</h2>
    <p>Location and motion permissions are used for trip tracking and optional trip nudges. Camera and photo access are used when you choose to capture or attach receipt and pay-statement images. Calendar access is used only if you choose to add HMRC deadline reminders.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>Okkle does not sell personal data. Your records are stored on your device unless you choose to export, back up or share them. If you send feedback, your message, optional screenshot and non-sensitive diagnostics are sent by email to Okkle support.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>Deleting Data</h2>
    <p>You can delete individual trips or records in the app. To delete all local app data, open Settings &gt; Data &amp; backup, then tap Delete all my data. Deleting app data does not remove files you previously exported, backed up or shared outside Okkle.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>Okkle is not intended for children under 13.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-panel">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy, support or data deletion help, email <a href="mailto:admin@okklelab.com">admin@okklelab.com</a>.</p>
  </section>
</div>
